    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i know people love me. i know. but love doesn't pay the mortgage or fix the credit score. it feels so selfish to stay and just keep watching them suffer because of my mistakes. it almost feels like the only way to actually be \"selfless\" would be to just stop being the problem. to just remove myself so they can actually breathe again. does that make sense? like, isn't it more logical to want to fix the problem for them?",
